stylometry: Integer programming models involve a constraint that a given variable must have a value that can be expressed as an integer.  These models are more difficult because they can be non-linear and have local maxima and minima, as well as global maxima and minima.  These models are more difficult to solve because they can have a range of possible solutions, and excel can take a long time to find an optimal one.  Even if an optimal solution is found, it may be a local maximum or minimum.  The algorithm uses a branch and bound method to find solutions.  The branches are possible optimal solutions.  Excel explores a branch only if it seems likely to produce an optimal solution.  When dealing with 0-1 models, we are often examining whether it is worth incurring fixed costs for a given product (whether to produce).
